-- Singapore's United Envirotech says in talks with potential buyer
-- By Rujun Shen
-- Wed Jul 02, 2014 01:33AM EDT
-- None



SINGAPORE, July 2 (Reuters) - United Envirotech Ltd <UNIT.SI>, a Singapore-based water treatment company, said on Wednesday it was in talks with a potential buyer, but did not give any details. [ID:nSNZ98wdQJ]

United Envirotech has a market capitalisation of about $1 billion. KKR China Water Investment Holdings Ltd is its biggest shareholder. Companies listed on the Singapore exchange have become takeover targets recently, with the total size of these deals so far this year reaching a record $13 billion. [ID:nL4N0OR0OD] Companies that are in discussion with potential buyers include STATS ChipPac Ltd <STTS.SI>, a semiconductor firm controlled by Singapore's state investor Temasek Holdings [TEM.UL]. Shares in United Envirotech last traded at S$1.465, up nearly 62 percent so far this year. The trading of shares will resume at 0700 GMT.